                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a weaver; I was coming past Watling-street, on the 7th of March, about seven in the evening; I saw James Rose following the prisoner and calling out stop thief! I stopped, at first I was going to lay hold of 
               <persName id="t17940430-107-person1093">
                  James
                   Rose
               <interp inst="t17940430-107-person1093" type="surname" value="Rose"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17940430-107-person1093" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17940430-107-person1093" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , just at the juncture of time 
               <persName id="t17940430-107-person1094">
                  James
                   Rose
               <interp inst="t17940430-107-person1094" type="surname" value="Rose"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17940430-107-person1094" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17940430-107-person1094" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             tumbled the prisoner down, and I assisted 
               <persName id="t17940430-107-person1095">
                  James
                   Rose
               <interp inst="t17940430-107-person1095" type="surname" value="Rose"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17940430-107-person1095" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17940430-107-person1095" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             in securing him, and took charge of him as constable of Cordwainers Ward.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17940430-107-verdict595" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17940430-107-verdict595" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
